content.text:
Here’s what changed.

### No inner `<button>`
- **`Item`** still uses **`asChild`**, but the child is now a **`div`** with **`role="button"`**, **`tabIndex={0}`**, **`onClick`**, and **`onKeyDown`** for **Enter** and **Space** (with **`preventDefault`** on Space so the page doesn’t scroll).
- Keeps the same **`aria-label`** as before.

### Clearly interactive
- **`cursor-pointer`**, **`hover:bg-muted/80`**, **`active:bg-muted`**, and the same **focus-visible ring** pattern as other controls so rows read as clickable even though they aren’t `<a>`/`<button>`.

### Chevron / “opens to the right”
- This app doesn’t depend on **`lucide-react`** (only **`@hugeicons/...`**), so the affordance uses **`ArrowRight01Icon`** from **`@hugeicons/core-free-icons`** with **`HugeiconsIcon`** (same pattern as menus/breadcrumbs in **`@procertus-ui/ui`**).
- Placed in **`ItemActions`** after the status **`Badge`**, **`size={16}`**, **`iconStroke(16)`**, **`text-muted-foreground`**, **`aria-hidden`**.

